# aihaus on Cursor

aihaus is multi-platform: Cursor and Claude Code are both first-class install targets
(see `pkg/.aihaus/decisions.md` ADR-005). This rules file documents which parts of aihaus
run on Cursor today and which stay Claude-Code-only because of primitive gaps.

## What works unmodified

Cursor reads `.claude/skills/` and `.claude/agents/` as legacy-compat paths.
aihaus's installer symlinks `.claude/skills` → `.aihaus/skills` and
`.claude/agents` → `.aihaus/agents`, so after the standard install, any
aihaus skill or agent that does NOT depend on the contradicted primitives
(see below) is addressable from Cursor without changes.

Safe-to-run surface (focus: read-only + single-turn flows):

- `/aih-help` — prints the command list. Pure read.
- `/aih-init` — reads codebase, writes `project.md`. Cursor will prompt for
  the write; accept to use.
- `/aih-quick` — parent-agent implementation path. Cursor will prompt per
  write; expected. Spawns `code-reviewer` (read-only) at the end.
- `/aih-plan` — research + plan authoring. Writes `PLAN.md` only. Safe.
- `/aih-brainstorm` — in single-turn conversational mode (the default).
  Panel/research/synthesis modes spawn multiple subagents; see matrix.
- Read-only research agents — `advisor-researcher`, `phase-researcher`,
  `domain-researcher`, `project-researcher`, `ui-researcher`,
  `ai-researcher`, `framework-selector`, `assumptions-analyzer`,
  `codebase-mapper`, `pattern-mapper`, `user-profiler`, `contrarian`.

Consult `COMPAT-MATRIX.md` for the full per-item verdict.

## Tool translation

When aihaus skills refer to invoking a subagent, the Claude Code and Cursor
conventions differ slightly. The semantics match; the vehicle names differ.

| Claude Code | Cursor |
|-------------|--------|
| `Agent` tool with `subagent_type: <name>` | `Task` tool with `/<name>` mention |
| `userPromptSubmit` hook event | `beforeSubmitPrompt` hook event |
| `subagentStart` / `subagentStop` | `subagentStart` / `subagentStop` (same) |
| `preToolUse` / `postToolUse` | `preToolUse` / `postToolUse` (same) |
| Parallel fan-out via multiple `Agent` calls in one turn | Parallel fan-out via multiple `Task` calls in one turn |

Hook surface is otherwise directly portable — Cursor hooks use the same
stdin-JSON + exit-2-to-block contract that Claude Code hooks use.

## Not supported

The following flows are Claude-Code-only and should NOT be invoked from
Cursor. Reasons cite specific primitive gaps verified 2026-04-14 against
Cursor documentation (see `.aihaus/research/cursor-primitives-verification.md`).

- **`/aih-run` milestone execution** — Drives the autonomous-commit machinery.
  Depends on `implementer` / `frontend-dev` / `code-fixer` subagents whose
  safety model requires `isolation: worktree` + `permissionMode:
  bypassPermissions`. Neither primitive exists on Cursor.

- **`implementer`, `frontend-dev`, `code-fixer`, `executor`, `nyquist-auditor`
  agents** — Declare `isolation: worktree` in frontmatter. Cursor subagent
  frontmatter does not accept an `isolation` field; the subagent would run
  without worktree isolation — a safety-model regression we will not
  silently ship.

- **Anything relying on `permissionMode: bypassPermissions`** — Cursor's
  only subagent permission primitive is `readonly: true` (the opposite of
  bypass). A write-capable aihaus subagent would hit Cursor's permission
  UI on every write. That is not "degraded but functional" — it defeats
  the purpose of autonomous milestone execution, where the operator has
  already consented to a full run.

- **Per-subagent tool whitelists as a safety guarantee** — Cursor subagents
  inherit all parent tools. aihaus agents that declare
  `tools: [Read, Grep, Glob]` (e.g., `contrarian`) will function on Cursor
  but the read-only discipline becomes prompt-level rather than tool-level.
  Listed as WORKS-WITH-CAVEAT in the matrix.

See `COMPAT-MATRIX.md` (sibling file) for the per-skill and per-agent verdict
with reasons and a last-verified date.

